All 3 files compile clean. Here's what was done:

✅ evaluator.py — Created
New node that runs after all workers finish:

Groups worker_results by sub_question, keeping only the latest attempt (so old low-confidence results don't trigger infinite retries)
For each latest result with confidence < 0.5 AND retries < 2, calls the LLM to reformulate the query
Returns {"retries": [...]} which merges into state['retries'] via operator.add
The route_retry function (already in workers.py) reads that list and fans out Send("search_worker", ...) for each retry.

✅ workers.py — Fixed
search_worker now respects _retries and _original passed from Send():

_retries: retry count (0 on first run, incremented on retry)
_original: the original sub-question (so the final result always reports the original, even after reformulation)
✅ react_agent.py — Fixed
Graph wiring is now:

Removed the search_worker → END duplicate edge — now the graph only ends when evaluate_worker → route_retry returns Send("__end__", {}).

Graph flow for retry edge



--
Phaase 3 is done
Worker returns confidence=0.3
         ↓
evaluate_worker: sees it's < 0.5, retries=0 < 2
         ↓  calls LLM to reformulate
         ↓  returns {"retries": [{reformulated_query, original, retries: 1}]}
         ↓
route_retry: reads retries list
         ↓
  → [Send("search_worker", {sub_question: reformulated, _original: ..., _retries: 1})]
         ↓
search_worker runs again with better query, returns result with retries=1
         ↓
evaluate_worker checks again — if still low but retries=1 < 2, tries one more time
         ↓
After 2 retries (or good confidence), route_retry returns Send("__end__", {}) → DONE


